sure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130941618,imgsize-747218.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[“You will be dead forever”: Sneako posts disturbing messages after Australia reportedly issues lifetime ban against streamer]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130936040.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Streamer Nico “Sneako” Kenn De Balinthazy shared another cryptic message on X saying, “I am ready to die,” after reports claimed Australia banned him from entering the country. Sneako denied being deported and later claimed federal agents followed him during his visit. His latest posts have gained major attention because of repeated death-themed messages shared over the past two weeks.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/you-will-be-dead-forever-sneako-posts-disturbing-messages-after-australia-reportedly-issues-lifetime-ban-against-streamer/articleshow/130936040.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/you-will-be-dead-forever-sneako-posts-disturbing-messages-after-australia-reportedly-issues-lifetime-ban-against-streamer/articleshow/130936040.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-08T05:58:49+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sehjal Gupta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130935974,imgsize-645760.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[NASA’s new plasma engine could reduce travel time to Mars]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130908505.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/nasas-new-plasma-engine-could-reduce-travel-time-to-mars/articleshow/130908505.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/nasas-new-plasma-engine-could-reduce-travel-time-to-mars/articleshow/130908505.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-08T03:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130910230,imgsize-71218.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA["He just kissed me": IShowSpeed left horrified as chaotic livestream moment explodes across social media]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130934326.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A viral clip from IShowSpeed’s Dominican Republic livestream has sparked massive online discussion after a fan unexpectedly tried to kiss the streamer during a crowded bus interaction. Security quickly intervened, while the shocked creator repeatedly questioned what was happening on stream. The chaotic moment spread rapidly across Reddit and X, with many viewers defending Speed. The controversy grew further after xQc suggested the livestream’s reported 1.1 million viewers may have been inflated by bots.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/he-just-kissed-me-ishowspeed-left-horrified-as-chaotic-livestream-moment-explodes-across-social-media/articleshow/130934326.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/he-just-kissed-me-ishowspeed-left-horrified-as-chaotic-livestream-moment-explodes-across-social-media/articleshow/130934326.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-08T05:32:50+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Barsha Dutta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130934326,imgsize-57972.cms"/></item></channel></rss>